<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-935] PassThrough Transport bug fixes-1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-935</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi&lt;br/&gt;
  Please find the patch file which contains fixes for following scenario.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Property mediator to be content aware based the given scope definition.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Fixed bugs when working with binary messages in RelayUtils.&lt;br/&gt;
3. BufferFacory re-factored (adding buffer cleanup operation), found the shared buffer not cleanup properly due to high load tests thus,it causes run time exceptions.&lt;br/&gt;
4.  Fix for CHUNKING_DISABLE for lager messages (tested messages such as 100k)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  Did run integration test after applying the patch attached herewith and seems all integration test have passed successfully.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      Meantime there are some fixes I have done for content switching issues and some fixes for RESTful services invocation, will provide those patches in different jira.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;br/&gt;
Dushan&lt;/p&gt;</description>
